1
00:00:12,083 --> 00:00:15,291
So, uh... Listen, Coconuts.

2
00:00:15,375 --> 00:00:16,958
You may not have
noticed on the account

3
00:00:17,041 --> 00:00:21,125
that you're kinda oblivious,
but this has been bothering me!

4
00:00:21,208 --> 00:00:23,375
You need to be honest here.

5
00:00:26,458 --> 00:00:32,458
[SAYA] Why is your shop
so run down looking?

6
00:00:35,833 --> 00:00:38,958
[KOKONOTSU] It's been
three months since then.

7
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:42,666
You think so?

8
00:00:42,750 --> 00:00:45,416
Duh, of course! It's like
a hobo snack shop!

9
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:47,833
[KOKONOTSU] Maybe, but we
seem to be managing somehow,

10
00:00:47,916 --> 00:00:48,958
so don't worry!

11
00:00:49,041 --> 00:00:49,791
See ya!

12
00:00:49,875 --> 00:00:52,208
Hey, wait! Jeez, seriously?

13
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:57,958
Is their shop really okay?

14
00:00:58,041 --> 00:00:59,375
Yo, I'm home!

15
00:00:59,458 --> 00:01:00,666
[groans]

16
00:01:00,750 --> 00:01:03,875
[YO]
The shop is a lost cause.

17
00:01:03,958 --> 00:01:06,000
Oh, welcome home.

18
00:01:06,083 --> 00:01:08,125
A lost cause?

19
00:01:11,375 --> 00:01:16,125
[YO] I think... it's time
to admit we're done for.

20
00:01:19,375 --> 00:01:22,083
[YO]
Are you okay?

21
00:01:22,166 --> 00:01:25,666
Like, your eyes are even
more dead than usual.

22
00:01:25,750 --> 00:01:30,708
♪


23
00:02:57,166 --> 00:03:00,375
Look, there's no easy way to
say this, so I'll just be blunt.

24
00:03:00,458 --> 00:03:02,333
We don't have that
many customers.

25
00:03:02,416 --> 00:03:05,375
No customers means no money.

26
00:03:05,458 --> 00:03:07,041
And no money means
there's no way

27
00:03:07,125 --> 00:03:09,958
to afford repairs around here.

28
00:03:10,041 --> 00:03:12,833
You're not even
listening, are you?

29
00:03:12,916 --> 00:03:16,208
[KOKONOTSU] Honestly,
I already knew all that.

30
00:03:16,291 --> 00:03:20,041
Deep down, I had
known for a while.

31
00:03:20,125 --> 00:03:22,541
But for some reason,
I had this idea

32
00:03:22,625 --> 00:03:25,500
that things would work
out if I stuck around.

33
00:03:26,708 --> 00:03:29,083
[YO]
Earth to Kokonotsu?

34
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:32,500
[KOKONOTSU]
I was waiting for it.

35
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:37,625
[KOKONOTSU]
Just waiting.

36
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:42,291
[HOTARU]
I'd like you to keep this.

37
00:03:42,375 --> 00:03:43,041
[gasps]

38
00:03:43,125 --> 00:03:44,625
Uh. You can't!

39
00:03:44,708 --> 00:03:46,958
Please, you can't go
out of business, Dad!

40
00:03:47,041 --> 00:03:48,291
I don't want to.

41
00:03:48,375 --> 00:03:49,833
I've got a free bar!

42
00:03:49,916 --> 00:03:52,041
A winner can only be exchanged
at the <i>dagashi</i> store

43
00:03:52,125 --> 00:03:53,583
where it was purchased!

44
00:03:55,916 --> 00:03:57,583
You know what?

45
00:03:57,666 --> 00:04:00,458
I like that determined
look on your face.

46
00:04:04,208 --> 00:04:07,291
Aha. It's Hotaru's, isn't it?

47
00:04:07,375 --> 00:04:08,625
[KOKONOTSU]
Uh.

48
00:04:08,708 --> 00:04:10,166
[YO]
I've seen it.

49
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,750
Sometimes you take the Homerun
Bar stick out of the drawer

50
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:15,041
and stare at it when
you think you're alone.

51
00:04:15,125 --> 00:04:17,791
That's why I think its Hotaru's.

52
00:04:17,875 --> 00:04:19,208
[yelps]

53
00:04:19,291 --> 00:04:21,416
[YO] You're lucky I'm the
only one who's caught you.

54
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:22,750
If someone else saw
you doin' that,

55
00:04:22,833 --> 00:04:25,750
they'd think you were a
total creeper, Konkonotsu.

56
00:04:25,833 --> 00:04:30,333
What the hell?! The only
creeper here is you!

57
00:04:30,416 --> 00:04:32,875
[YO]
Very well, let's do it.

58
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:38,041
It's time to revive...
our snack shop!

59
00:04:38,125 --> 00:04:39,583
For real?

60
00:04:41,083 --> 00:04:44,291
Right, first off, let's
clean up the store!

61
00:04:44,375 --> 00:04:46,166
[KOKONOTSU]
Yeah!

62
00:04:46,250 --> 00:04:49,000
Come on, Dad, first
one outside wins!

63
00:04:49,083 --> 00:04:50,416
Hurry up, ya slowpoke!

64
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:51,750
[YO]
I am!

65
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:55,041
Hey, no running
inside, remember?

66
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:07,541
[YO screaming]

67
00:05:07,625 --> 00:05:10,583
[KOKONOTSU] And that's how
Dad wound up in the hospital.

68
00:05:10,666 --> 00:05:12,708
For a whole month.

69
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:17,000
[YO] Try to hang in
there while I'm gone.

70
00:05:17,083 --> 00:05:18,458
You've got this.

71
00:05:18,541 --> 00:05:20,875
It's nothing you
can't handle, son.

72
00:05:20,958 --> 00:05:24,500
Oops, I mean,
Manager Kokonostu.

73
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:29,625
[KOKONOTSU]
It is shabby.

74
00:05:29,708 --> 00:05:34,125
It's not like I
hadn't noticed it.

75
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:38,833
I guess I was just pre-occupied
by Hotaru's disappearance.

76
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:41,875
[KOKONOTSU]
Why?

77
00:05:45,416 --> 00:05:48,375
[SAYA] To, I'm really
worried about Coconuts.

78
00:05:48,458 --> 00:05:51,083
I mean, like his eyes have
always looked pretty dead,

79
00:05:51,166 --> 00:05:53,958
but lately, they're worse
than those deep sea fish.

80
00:05:54,041 --> 00:05:58,041
Wow, spoken like a true friend.
Although, you might be right.

81
00:05:58,125 --> 00:06:01,458
I know. We should go
try to cheer him up.

82
00:06:01,541 --> 00:06:04,166
Oh, but whatever you do,
don't bring up Hotaru.

83
00:06:04,250 --> 00:06:06,750
He makes super weird faces
whenever she's mentioned.

84
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:09,625
That sounds fun
though! I wanna see.

85
00:06:09,708 --> 00:06:14,083
Hi, uh, it's kinda messy,
but you guys can come in.

86
00:06:14,166 --> 00:06:15,166
I'm cleaning.

87
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:16,833
[SAYA]
Uh.

88
00:06:16,916 --> 00:06:18,791
He seems okay.

89
00:06:18,875 --> 00:06:21,583
Um. Sorry if I made you worry.

90
00:06:21,666 --> 00:06:23,333
[SAYA]
Well, I was pretty worried.

91
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:26,208
I feel like a jerk for
making you guys help me.

92
00:06:26,291 --> 00:06:27,708
It's all good, man!

93
00:06:27,791 --> 00:06:30,625
We just feel bad that
Hotaru ditched you-- Ah!

94
00:06:31,875 --> 00:06:33,500
[SAYA]
Shut your dumb face!

95
00:06:33,583 --> 00:06:34,625
Uh. Sorry.

96
00:06:34,708 --> 00:06:35,708
[KOKONOTSU chuckles]

97
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:37,708
Well, I'm okay now.

98
00:06:37,791 --> 00:06:39,833
Besides, I'm sure
she'll come back.

99
00:06:39,916 --> 00:06:41,583
I've made up my mind.

100
00:06:41,666 --> 00:06:44,375
I am gonna make this
shop better than ever!

101
00:06:44,458 --> 00:06:46,000
Good, Coconuts.

102
00:06:47,166 --> 00:06:49,458
Plus, if we don't start
making some money,

103
00:06:49,541 --> 00:06:51,625
the only food I'll
have is this <i>dagashi</i> .

104
00:06:51,708 --> 00:06:54,583
Why did you wait for things
to get that desperate?

105
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:02,250
I'm gonna take this
to the dumpster.

106
00:07:02,333 --> 00:07:03,291
[KOKONOTSU]
Thanks!

107
00:07:05,625 --> 00:07:08,750
Let's see. What goes
after the <i>umaibo</i> ?

108
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:11,333
Hey, do you remember, Coconuts?

109
00:07:11,416 --> 00:07:13,083
[KOKONOTSU]
"Get a Move On, You Cod!"

110
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:14,125
[grunts]

111
00:07:15,208 --> 00:07:17,875
[SAYA]
Seriously? What the heck?

112
00:07:17,958 --> 00:07:23,291
Was I being slow?
No, I wasn't, right?

113
00:07:23,375 --> 00:07:26,333
And even if I was being slow,
where does he get off

114
00:07:26,416 --> 00:07:28,458
calling me a freakin' cod
when I'm over here

115
00:07:28,541 --> 00:07:32,000
sacrificing my free time to
help him clean up his shop?

116
00:07:33,458 --> 00:07:34,875
[KOKONOTSU]
Did you hear me, Saya?

117
00:07:34,958 --> 00:07:36,083
[growls]

118
00:07:36,166 --> 00:07:38,875
[KOKONOTSU]
Ah! What? What did I do?

119
00:07:39,916 --> 00:07:42,458
[SAYA]
"Get a Move On, You Cod!"

120
00:07:42,541 --> 00:07:44,375
[KOKONOTSU] Its name is a
play on the word "cod."

121
00:07:44,458 --> 00:07:46,958
Besides snacking, it's
also used as a side dish.

122
00:07:47,041 --> 00:07:48,625
[SAYA chuckles]

123
00:07:48,708 --> 00:07:49,916
Uh, sorry.

124
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,708
Give it a try. It's quite
popular with adults.

125
00:07:52,791 --> 00:07:55,625
They eat it while drinking,
and some use it in soups.

126
00:07:58,708 --> 00:08:00,958
You're right! It's delicious!

127
00:08:01,041 --> 00:08:05,625
Still though, that's one heck
of a name and illustration.

128
00:08:05,708 --> 00:08:08,208
And here, look on the
back of the package.

129
00:08:08,291 --> 00:08:10,500
It says, "Let's have
a bite and shout,

130
00:08:10,583 --> 00:08:13,166
'Get a move on, you cod!'"

131
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:15,583
Do you think... we're
supposed to do this?

132
00:08:15,666 --> 00:08:17,083
Huh? Are we?

133
00:08:17,166 --> 00:08:20,208
Nah! Of course not,
it'd be embarrassing!

134
00:08:21,625 --> 00:08:24,333
[BOTH laughing]

135
00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:29,208
[SAYA] Not that it would
ever stop Hotaru.

136
00:08:29,291 --> 00:08:35,041
I wonder, why did she up
and leave town so suddenly?

137
00:08:35,125 --> 00:08:38,458
Maybe Coconuts
knows why she left.

138
00:08:38,541 --> 00:08:41,791
It's been a while since
we've hung out like this.

139
00:08:41,875 --> 00:08:44,458
Talkin' about <i>dagashi</i> and stuff.

140
00:08:44,541 --> 00:08:47,041
I know I've been acting weird,

141
00:08:47,125 --> 00:08:50,458
but I also know you've been
trying to cheer me up lately.

142
00:08:50,541 --> 00:08:52,125
Saya.

143
00:08:52,208 --> 00:08:53,333
Thank you.

144
00:08:54,958 --> 00:08:56,958
Uh.

145
00:08:57,041 --> 00:08:59,375
I didn't do anything
that special.

146
00:08:59,458 --> 00:09:01,958
[KOKONOTSU] You've helped
more than you know.

147
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:03,125
Anyway...

148
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:04,333
[KOKONOTSU chuckles]

149
00:09:04,416 --> 00:09:06,666
I'm a little embarrassed!

150
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:09,500
[SAYA]
Ah! I'm so happy right now!

151
00:09:09,583 --> 00:09:11,791
I could literally die
from happiness.

152
00:09:11,875 --> 00:09:15,000
[TO] Hey, guys! Check it!
There's this crazy cat outside.

153
00:09:15,083 --> 00:09:16,250
Oh, you're back!

154
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:18,833
How was the trash run?

155
00:09:18,916 --> 00:09:22,000
Wait. Why does this
feel awkward?

156
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:23,125
Huh? It's not!

157
00:09:23,208 --> 00:09:26,666
Yeah! We were just talkin'!

158
00:09:28,291 --> 00:09:30,500
"You wanna get your
groove on, you cods?"

159
00:09:30,583 --> 00:09:34,541
[SAYA] More like "How 'bout
you get a clue, you moron!"?

160
00:09:34,625 --> 00:09:36,916
[TO] Man, this place
looks a lot better!

161
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:40,916
[SAYA] Yeah! It's back
to its former glory!

162
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,333
[KOKONOTSU]
Mh-hm!

163
00:09:44,791 --> 00:09:47,958
Hold on. I have to
do better than this.

164
00:09:48,041 --> 00:09:50,666
I can't just keep
everything the same.

165
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:52,500
I need some fresh ideas.

166
00:09:52,583 --> 00:09:55,833
What do customers want?
What's convenient for them?

167
00:09:55,916 --> 00:09:59,875
I have to try and put
myself in their shoes.

168
00:09:59,958 --> 00:10:00,708
Whoa.

169
00:10:00,791 --> 00:10:02,708
Dude, you sound kinda cool.

170
00:10:02,791 --> 00:10:03,541
[KOKONOTSU]
Huh?

171
00:10:03,625 --> 00:10:05,041
[chuckles]

172
00:10:05,125 --> 00:10:06,750
It's true!

173
00:10:06,833 --> 00:10:08,791
<i>Dagashi</i> customers are thinking
about more than just snacks

174
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:10,791
when they're here shopping.

175
00:10:10,875 --> 00:10:14,083
From plastic models,
to stationery supplies.

176
00:10:14,166 --> 00:10:17,041
The thing is, <i>dagashi</i> shops
are like the forerunner

177
00:10:17,125 --> 00:10:19,000
to convenience stores.

178
00:10:19,083 --> 00:10:21,666
Hey, there's an idea!

179
00:10:21,750 --> 00:10:24,458
We don't have any convenience
stores around here!

180
00:10:24,541 --> 00:10:27,250
If I can just
capitalize on that...

181
00:10:28,708 --> 00:10:30,125
[SAYA]
Um, Coconuts?

182
00:10:30,208 --> 00:10:31,583
[KOKONOTSU]
Hm?

183
00:10:31,666 --> 00:10:34,541
So, uh, about that...

184
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:39,333
[KOKONOTSU]
What?

185
00:10:39,416 --> 00:10:40,916
What?

186
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,666
What?!

187
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:46,125
There's a new
convenience store?!

188
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:53,458
♪


189
00:12:18,666 --> 00:12:19,833
[SAYA]
Next time:

190
00:12:19,916 --> 00:12:22,125
"Convenience Store,
Job Magazine, and..."

191
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:25,083
Oh, no! This could be bad
for your <i>dagashi</i> shop!

